How to use this book

This book plays Hangman with you. Think of a noun, and the book will attempt to guess the word you're thinking of just like a regular game of hangman - by asking you about letters one at a time.

To do this, you need to follow a couple of simple rules. First, think of a noun. On the next page, you'll be shown what section to look up based on the number of letters in your word.

From there on, each section will start by guessing a letter. Consult the table in that section to see what page you should turn to based on where that letter appears in your word.

If the book guesses your word, it wins! If the book makes a guess, and you don't see an option in the table that matches your word, you win - the book doesn't know the word you're thinking of.
